BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//Bali Festivals//Felix//EN
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
METHOD:PUBLISH
X-WR-CALNAME:Bali Festivals & Holidays
X-WR-CALDESC:Balinese ceremonies and Indonesian public holidays, with notes on where it is most beautiful. Curated edition. 2027 national/Islamic dates are predictions and may shift by government decree.
X-WR-TIMEZONE:Asia/Makassar
REFRESH-INTERVAL;VALUE=DURATION:PT12H
X-PUBLISHED-TTL:PT12H
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pengerupukan-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260318
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260319
SUMMARY:Ogoh-ogoh Parade (Pengerupukan) — Nyepi Eve
DESCRIPTION:The most photogenic night of the year. Villages parade giant demon effigies (ogoh-ogoh) built over weeks\, then burn them to drive out evil before the Day of Silence.\n\nBest viewing: Denpasar (Catur Muka crossing) for scale\, Ubud for craft\, your own banjar for intimacy. Go early evening — expect road closures and crowds.
LOCATION:Across Bali (Denpasar\, Ubud)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:nyepi-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260319
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260320
SUMMARY:Nyepi — Balinese Day of Silence (New Year)
DESCRIPTION:The island shuts down for 24h: no flights\, no lights\, no going outside — even for tourists. Airport closed. Stay in your villa or hotel with meals sorted in advance.\n\nThe payoff: at night\, with every light off island-wide\, the stars are extraordinary.
LOCATION:All of Bali
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eid-fitr-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260320
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260323
SUMMARY:Eid al-Fitr (Idul Fitri) — Public Holiday
DESCRIPTION:National holiday period (approx 20–22 March). Falls right after Nyepi this year. Banks and government offices close\, domestic flights and ferries fill up. Date may shift +/- a day by government decree.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:good-friday-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260403
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260404
SUMMARY:Good Friday (Public Holiday)
DESCRIPTION:National public holiday. Quiet day\, minimal impact on travel.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:labour-day-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260502
SUMMARY:Labour Day (Public Holiday)
DESCRIPTION:National public holiday.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ascension-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260514
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260515
SUMMARY:Ascension Day of Jesus (Public Holiday)
DESCRIPTION:National public holiday. Often creates a long weekend — expect busier roads and beaches.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eid-adha-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260527
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260528
SUMMARY:Eid al-Adha (Idul Adha) — Public Holiday
DESCRIPTION:National holiday. Date may shift +/- a day by government decree.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:waisak-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260531
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260601
SUMMARY:Waisak (Vesak) Day — Public Holiday
DESCRIPTION:Buddhist holiday marking the birth\, enlightenment and death of Buddha. Low-key in Bali\; the grand celebration is at Borobudur in Java.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pancasila-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Pancasila Day (Public Holiday)
DESCRIPTION:National public holiday honouring Indonesia's founding philosophy.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:islamic-new-year-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260616
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260617
SUMMARY:Islamic New Year (1 Muharram) — Public Holiday
DESCRIPTION:National public holiday. Coincides with Penampahan Galungan this year. Date may shift by government decree.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:penampahan-galungan-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260616
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260617
SUMMARY:Penampahan Galungan — Preparation Day
DESCRIPTION:Families raise penjor (tall decorated bamboo poles)\, make lawar\, and ready offerings. Streets fill with penjor through the evening — golden hour the day before Galungan is prime for photos and FPV.
LOCATION:Villages across Bali
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:galungan-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260617
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260618
SUMMARY:Galungan — Victory of Good over Evil
DESCRIPTION:Bali's homecoming festival — ancestral spirits return to family homes\, dharma triumphs over adharma. Penjor line every street.\n\nThis is a village and temple event\, not a beach-club one. Densest and most beautiful: Ubud\, Sidemen\, Gianyar. Dress respectfully (sarong + sash) near temples.\n\nNote: 2026 has only ONE Galungan all year — rare.
LOCATION:Ubud\, Sidemen\, Gianyar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kuningan-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260627
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260628
SUMMARY:Kuningan — Spirits Return to the Heavens
DESCRIPTION:Closing of the Galungan cycle. Yellow dominates: nasi kuning offerings and tamiang coconut-leaf shields. Ceremonies wrap by midday — go in the morning. Quieter and more tender than Galungan day.
LOCATION:Temples across Bali
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:umanis-kuningan-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260628
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260629
SUMMARY:Umanis Kuningan — The Day After
DESCRIPTION:The relaxed day after. Families visit scenic spots and water temples. A calm day to photograph temple life without the peak-day intensity.
LOCATION:Water temples (Tirta Empul\, Ulun Danu Beratan)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:independence-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260817
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260818
SUMMARY:Indonesian Independence Day (Merdeka)
DESCRIPTION:National holiday. Flag ceremonies\, village games (panjat pinang — greased-pole climbing)\, red-and-white everywhere. Expect heavier traffic and busier domestic flights.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:christmas-2026@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261225
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261226
SUMMARY:Christmas Day (Public Holiday)
DESCRIPTION:National public holiday. Peak tourist season begins — book everything early\, beaches and Ubud get crowded.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:new-year-2027@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270102
SUMMARY:New Year's Day (Public Holiday)
DESCRIPTION:National public holiday. Peak season — Canggu\, Seminyak and Uluwatu are packed.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:penampahan-galungan-2027a@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270112
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270113
SUMMARY:Penampahan Galungan — Preparation Day
DESCRIPTION:Prep day before Galungan. Penjor go up across villages through the evening — best light for photos the day before.
LOCATION:Villages across Bali
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:galungan-2027a@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270113
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270114
SUMMARY:Galungan — Victory of Good over Evil
DESCRIPTION:Bali's homecoming festival. Penjor line every street\; richest in Ubud\, Sidemen\, Gianyar. Dress respectfully near temples.\n\nNote: 2027 has TWO Galungan — this one in January and another on 11 August.
LOCATION:Ubud\, Sidemen\, Gianyar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kuningan-2027a@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270123
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270124
SUMMARY:Kuningan — Spirits Return to the Heavens
DESCRIPTION:Closing of the Galungan cycle. Yellow offerings and tamiang decorations. Ceremonies wrap by midday — go in the morning.
LOCATION:Temples across Bali
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:umanis-kuningan-2027a@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270124
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270125
SUMMARY:Umanis Kuningan — The Day After
DESCRIPTION:The relaxed day after Kuningan. Good for calm temple photography.
LOCATION:Water temples (Tirta Empul\, Ulun Danu Beratan)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:chinese-new-year-2027@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270206
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270207
SUMMARY:Chinese New Year (Imlek) — Public Holiday
DESCRIPTION:National public holiday\, Year of the Goat. Most visible at Chinese temples (klenteng)\, e.g. in Denpasar. Date is fixed by the lunar calendar.
LOCATION:All of Indonesia
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pengerupukan-2027@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270308
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270309
SUMMARY:Ogoh-ogoh Parade (Pengerupukan) — Nyepi Eve
DESCRIPTION:The big ogoh-ogoh night before Nyepi. Giant demon effigies paraded and burned. Best: Denpasar for scale\, Ubud for craft. Go early evening\, expect road closures.
LOCATION:Across Bali (Denpasar\, Ubud)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:nyepi-2027@bali-festivals
DTSTAMP:20260629T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270309
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270310
SUMMARY:Nyepi — Balinese Day of Silence (New Year)
DESCRIPTION:The island shuts down for 24h: no flights\, no lights\, no going outside. Airport closed. Stay in with meals sorted. Brilliant stars at night with all lights off.
LOCATION:All of Bali
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
